{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SbsAHYT6XE6xLFoNVu8Yef","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All pods are healthy. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** Two broken permissions:\n1. `app-user` on `/app` had empty configure permission (`\"\"`) — write/read worked but queue/exchange declare was blocked.\n2. `ops-user` on `/ops` had no permissions at all.\n\n**Fix applied** (via `rabbitmqctl` directly on `rabbitmq-0`):\n- `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — restored full configure/write/read for app-user\n- `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted full configure/write/read for ops-user\n\n**Result:** Both `app-client` and `ops-client` are now `Running 1/1`, and the 3-node RabbitMQ cluster remains healthy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":31656,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":289},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"476af5e6-0924-4e5c-9f40-a0f9e816cec9","uuid":"f086beb5-50d9-4bf4-9726-8004e9d75f1c","request_id":"req_011CbzstRJCDFaPuqhkL18Lg"}
